reviews.text:
Another great lunch place in Kowloon Bay! Food Expression serves authentic Asian dishes, including Chinese, Korean, Singaporean and Thai cuisines. I visited during late lunch hour at 14:00, when quite a number of choices were sold out.

I ordered this Szechuan Slow-Cooked Chicken with Veggie Rice, which tasted as good as it looked. I adore the veggie rice. As a veggie hater, it’s a great way to uptake some fibers subtly without having to chew a lot.

As for the Szechuan slow-cooked chicken, it’s simply amazing! There was peanut sauce which went well with the numbing spicy chicken. The numbing spicy sauce had a bit of sweet and sour taste, interesting! The chicken was tender and meaty, and there was a whole chicken leg!

Since I visited during late lunch hour (14:00 - 16:00), there was a deal with a free drink and 20% off, so the whole lunch set only costed HK$47! Amazing deal!
